乳腺癌近距离治疗分为两种方式：
* 乳腺癌组织间插植近距离治疗应用多根插植导管
* 乳腺癌腔内近距离治疗应用球囊导管

乳腺癌组织间插植近距离治疗是将多根柔性塑料导管置于乳腺组织，并短时间停留。通过精确的定位，以获得对治疗区域的优化照射，同时避开临近的乳腺组织。<ref name="Kelley 2007" />导管与后装机连接，将制定的照射剂量传输到治疗区域。乳腺癌组织间插植近距离治疗可用于外照射治疗后的补量，或作为APBI的治疗方式。<ref name="Polgár-2009" />

乳腺癌腔内近距离治疗（也称作“球囊式近距离治疗”）是将单独的导管放置于肿瘤切除后 （乳房肿瘤切除术）留下的空腔内。<ref name="Kelley 2007" /> 导管可在术中或术后插入。<ref name="Kelley 2007" />  通过导管，空腔内的球囊被充满气。于是导管与{{link-en|后装机|#Procedure}}相连， 将照射剂量通过导管传输到球囊中。当前，乳腺癌腔内近距离治疗仅作为APBI的一种常规治疗方式。<ref name="Shah-2010">{{cite journal|title=A dosimetric analysis comparing electron beam with the MammoSite brachytherapy applicator for intact breast boost|pages=80–87|issn=1724-191X|journal=Physica medica: PM: an international journal devoted to the applications of physics to medicine and biology: official journal of the Italian Association of Biomedical Physics (AIFB)|volume=26|issue=2|date=2010-4|doi=10.1016/j.ejmp.2009.08.004|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19836283|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=A. P. Shah, J. B. Strauss, M. C. Kirk, S. S. Chen, A. Dickler|pmid=19836283|archive-date=2020-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200428053502/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19836283|dead-url=no}}</ref>

除此之外，还有一些乳腺癌近距离治疗装置，将组织间和腔内治疗的特点相结合（如：SAVI）。这些装置具有多根治疗导管，但仅通过单一入口进入乳腺，研究表明应用多根导管有利于医生更精确的照射靶区。<ref>Scanderbeg, D; Yashar, C; White, G; Rice, R; Pawlicki, T (2010). “Evaluation of Three APBI Techniques under NSABP B-39 Guidelines.” ''Journal of Applied Clinical Medical Physics'' 11 (1): 274-280.</ref><ref>Yashar, C; Blair, S; Wallace, A; Scanderbeg, D (2009). “Initial Clinical Experience with the Strut-Adjusted Volume Implant Brachytherapy Applicator for Accelerated Partial Breast Irradiation.” ''Brachytherapy'' 8: 367-372.</ref>

===皮肤癌===
高剂量率近距离治疗对于非黑素瘤的[[皮肤癌|皮肤癌]]，如[[基底细胞癌|基底细胞癌]]和[[鳞状细胞癌|鳞状细胞癌]]，提供了手术治疗以外的另一种治疗方式。尤其适用于鼻、耳、眼睑或唇等，进行手术会导致毁容或需要大面积重建的部位。<ref name="GEC-ESTRO-Skin" />可借助多种施源器，保证放射源与皮肤的近距离接触，与皮肤的曲面适形，并可有助于优化照射剂量的精确传输。<ref name="GEC-ESTRO-Skin" />

皮肤癌近距离治疗具有良好的美容效果及临床效能； 随访5年的研究显示近距离治疗对于局部控制十分有效，与外照射治疗效果相似。<ref name="Guix-2000">{{cite journal|title=Treatment of skin carcinomas of the face by high-dose-rate brachytherapy and custom-made surface molds|pages=95–102|issn=0360-3016|journal=International Journal of Radiation Oncology, Biology, Physics|volume=47|issue=1|date=2000-04-01|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10758310|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=B. Guix, F. Finestres, J. Tello, C. Palma, A. Martinez, J. Guix, R. Guix|pmid=10758310|archive-date=2020-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200428053507/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10758310|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Sedda-2008">{{cite journal|title=Dermatological high-dose-rate brachytherapy for the treatment of basal and squamous cell carcinoma|pages=745–749|issn=1365-2230|journal=Clinical and Experimental Dermatology|volume=33|issue=6|date=2008-11|doi=10.1111/j.1365-2230.2008.02852.x|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18681873|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=A. F. Sedda, G. Rossi, C. Cipriani, A. M. Carrozzo, P. Donati|pmid=18681873|archive-date=2020-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200428053512/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18681873|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Rio-2005">{{cite journal|title=Interstitial brachytherapy of periorificial skin carcinomas of the face: a retrospective study of 97 cases|pages=753–757|issn=0360-3016|journal=International Journal of Radiation Oncology, Biology, Physics|volume=63|issue=3|date=2005-11-01|doi=10.1016/j.ijrobp.2005.03.027|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15927410|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=Emmanuel Rio, Etienne Bardet, Christophe Ferron, Patrick Peuvrel, Stéphane Supiot, Loic Campion, Claude Beauvillain De Montreuil, Marc André Mahe, Brigitte Dreno|pmid=15927410|archive-date=2020-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200428053517/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15927410|dead-url=no}}</ref>治疗时间一般较短，为患者提供便利。<ref name="Musmacher-2006">
